title.narrative: Cross sectorial for multiple outcomes (health, Education, Child Protection) in the refugees camps Tindouf

description.narrative: UNICEF pursued the implementation of its pluriannual humanitarian programme in;Tindouf;in five main areas: immunization, neonatal/maternal care, education, youth and child rights&39; promotion and COVID-19 response. In 2021, the main achievements were: 21.000 children were vaccinated in the five Sahrawi refugee camps, 40.000 children provided with continuous education services through rehabilitated/constructed education facilities,;schools;supplies, trained teachers and health care. Another major result was the validation and dissemination of the Education 5-years strategy.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
